<section xml:id="C10.S4">
<title>Connection Formulas</title>        
   
<para xml:id="C10.S4.p1">

<sentence sentence-num-in-para="1" sentence-num-in-section="1" xml:id="C10.S4.p1.s1">
Other solutions of (10.2.1) include <Math mode="inline" xml:id="C10.S4.p1.m1">J_{-\nu}\left(z\right)</Math> , <Math mode="inline" xml:id="C10.S4.p1.m2">Y_{-\nu}\left(z\right)</Math> , <Math mode="inline" xml:id="C10.S4.p1.m3">{H^{(1)}_{-\nu}}\left(z\right)</Math> , and <Math mode="inline" xml:id="C10.S4.p1.m4">{H^{(2)}_{-\nu}}\left(z\right)</Math>.
</sentence>

<sentence sentence-num-in-para="2" sentence-num-in-section="2" xml:id="C10.S4.p1.s2">
<Math equation-number="10.4.1" mode="display" xml:id="C10.S4.E1">J_{-n}\left(z\right)=(-1)^{n}J_{n}\left(z\right),Y_{-n}\left(z\right)=(-1)^{n}Y_{n}\left(z\right),</Math> <Math equation-number="10.4.2" mode="display" xml:id="C10.S4.E2">{H^{(1)}_{-n}}\left(z\right)=(-1)^{n}{H^{(1)}_{n}}\left(z\right),{H^{(2)}_{-n}}\left(z\right)=(-1)^{n}{H^{(2)}_{n}}\left(z\right)</Math>.
</sentence>

<sentence sentence-num-in-para="3" sentence-num-in-section="3" xml:id="C10.S4.p1.s3">
<Math equation-number="10.4.3" mode="display" xml:id="C10.S4.E3">{H^{(1)}_{\nu}}\left(z\right)=J_{\nu}\left(z\right)+iY_{\nu}\left(z\right),{H^{(2)}_{\nu}}\left(z\right)=J_{\nu}\left(z\right)-iY_{\nu}\left(z\right),</Math> <Math equation-number="10.4.4" mode="display" xml:id="C10.S4.E4">J_{\nu}\left(z\right)=\frac{1}{2}\left({H^{(1)}_{\nu}}\left(z\right)+{H^{(2)}_ {\nu}}\left(z\right)\right),Y_{\nu}\left(z\right)=\frac{1}{2i}\left({H^{(1)}_{\nu}}\left(z\right)-{H^{(2)} _{\nu}}\left(z\right)\right)</Math>.
</sentence>

<sentence sentence-num-in-para="4" sentence-num-in-section="4" xml:id="C10.S4.p1.s4">
<Math equation-number="10.4.5" mode="display" xml:id="C10.S4.E5">J_{\nu}\left(z\right)=\csc\left(\nu\pi\right)\left(Y_{-\nu}\left(z\right)-Y_{ \nu}\left(z\right)\cos\left(\nu\pi\right)\right)</Math>.
</sentence>

<sentence sentence-num-in-para="5" sentence-num-in-section="5" xml:id="C10.S4.p1.s5">
<Math equation-number="10.4.6" mode="display" xml:id="C10.S4.E6">{H^{(1)}_{-\nu}}\left(z\right)=e^{\nu\pi i}{H^{(1)}_{\nu}}\left(z\right),{H^{(2)}_{-\nu}}\left(z\right)=e^{-\nu\pi i}{H^{(2)}_{\nu}}\left(z\right)</Math>.
</sentence>

<sentence sentence-num-in-para="6" sentence-num-in-section="6" xml:id="C10.S4.p1.s6">
<Math equation-number="10.4.7" mode="display" xml:id="C10.S4.E7">{H^{(1)}_{\nu}}\left(z\right)=i\csc\left(\nu\pi\right)\left(e^{-\nu\pi i}J_{ \nu}\left(z\right)-J_{-\nu}\left(z\right)\right)=\csc\left(\nu\pi\right)\left( Y_{-\nu}\left(z\right)-e^{-\nu\pi i}Y_{\nu}\left(z\right)\right),</Math> <Math equation-number="10.4.8" mode="display" xml:id="C10.S4.E8">{H^{(2)}_{\nu}}\left(z\right)=i\csc\left(\nu\pi\right)\left(J_{-\nu}\left(z \right)-e^{\nu\pi i}J_{\nu}\left(z\right)\right)=\csc\left(\nu\pi\right)\left( Y_{-\nu}\left(z\right)-e^{\nu\pi i}Y_{\nu}\left(z\right)\right)</Math>.
</sentence>

<sentence sentence-num-in-para="7" sentence-num-in-section="7" xml:id="C10.S4.p1.s7">
In (10.4.5), (10.4.7), and (10.4.8) limiting values are taken when <Math mode="inline" xml:id="C10.S4.p1.m5">\nu=n</Math> ; compare (10.2.3) and (10.2.4).
</sentence>

</para>
 
